bug.short_desc: Klick on "View Source" link in object or method description does not open the corresponding source line on github

long_desc.thetext:
Stumbled on this by searching in the current api viewer of master, where I tried to navigate to the source line on github by clicking on the "View Source" link.
To reproduce, open e.g.
http://demo.qooxdoo.org/current/apiviewer/#qx.core.Object
navigate to the "Constructor", click on the + sign to make the description visible. Then click on "View Source", which should open the source file from github, placing the cursor on the line where the implementation of the constructor begins. The result is that the file is being opened, but the line is allways line 1
This worked in qooxdoo 3.5.1 as expected:
http://demo.qooxdoo.org/3.5.1/apiviewer/index.html#qx.core.Object
qooxdoo 3.5.1 seems to be the last version where this worked.

Just tried in in chrome and it works as expected. Which browser do you use? Does your link look like this?
https://github.com/qooxdoo/qooxdoo/blob/release_4_1/framework/source/class/qx/core/Object.js#L56

You're right. It now works. Weird!
I've tried that before and the line parameter (L) was allways set to 1.
Sorry for the noise.
This was on Windows 7 x64 with Chrome 40.

This IS a bug. Now it is there again.
To reliably reproduce this I had to close the browser completely and navigate fresh to a given method e.g:
http://demo.qooxdoo.org/current/apiviewer/#qx.Class~hasProperty!method_public
by pasting the link above in the browser. Then open the method properties and inspect the "View Source" link target.
It shows now:
https://github.com/qooxdoo/qooxdoo/blob/release_4_1/framework/source/class/qx/Class.js#L1
See attached screenshot.
Tested with Chrome 40 and Firefox 35
Created attachment 1364 Screenshot showing the wrong link to the github source
Now I can reproduce it as well, thanks. :)

I just did some further investigation. A small set of methods in qx.Class do not work due to the fact that these methods are only a reference to another method. Take a look at hasProperty e.g.
https://github.com/qooxdoo/qooxdoo/blob/release_4_1/framework/source/class/qx/Class.js#L476
I tracked down the wrong line number back to the api data generation process which does not detect the right line number. The viewer itself seems to be ok as it only reads the line number from the data.
